                    }
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>You create a cloud of mesmerizing patterns and colors that hovers in the air. Creatures are @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Dazzled] while inside the cloud. In addition, a creature must attempt a Will saving throw if it is inside the cloud when you cast it, when it enters the cloud, when it ends its turn within the cloud, or if it uses a @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Seek] or Interact action on the cloud. A creature currently @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Fascinated] by hypnotize doesn't attempt new saves.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The target is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The target is fascinated by the cloud.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The target is fascinated by the cloud. While it remains fascinated, it can't use reactions.</p>"
                },
                "duration": {
                    "sustained": true,
                    "value": "1 minute"
